<HEAD>Polisario, Morocco Agree Conditionally To U.N. Peace Plan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GENEVA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Morocco </LOCATION> and the Polisario guerrillas said today they had agreed conditionally to a <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> peace plan aimed at ending their 13-year conflict in the <LOCATION> Western </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Sahara </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Francois </PERSON> <PERSON> Giuliani </PERSON> said both sides `` accepted with remarks and comments'' the Aug. 11 peace plan for a cease-fire and a U.N.-monitored referendum in the phosphate-rich desert territory. The text of the proposal has not been made public. The Marxist-led Polisario has fought for <LOCATION> Western </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Sahara </LOCATION>'s independence since 1975, when <LOCATION> Spain </LOCATION>'s colonial forces gave up the northwest African territory and <LOCATION> Morocco </LOCATION> annexed it <LOCATION> Algeria </LOCATION> has backed Polisario's campaign, but <LOCATION> Morocco </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Algeria </LOCATION> restored diplomatic relations in May after years of tension verging on war over the territory. In <LOCATION> Madrid </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Spanish </LOCATION> Foreign Minister <PERSON> Francisco </PERSON> <PERSON> Fernandez </PERSON> <PERSON> Ordonez </PERSON> told <ORGANIZATION> Spanish </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Radio </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Spain </ORGANIZATION> that he viewed as `` very good news'' the announcement. `` We expect this process to lead to the establishment of peace and prosperity in this region of great importance to <LOCATION> Spain </LOCATION>,'' the minister said. <PERSON> Giuliani </PERSON> said Secretary-General <PERSON> Javier </PERSON> <PERSON> Perez </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Cuellar </PERSON> expects to begin a <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> peacekeeping operation in the <LOCATION> Western </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Sahara </LOCATION> before the end of the year. The <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> is cons