e not Western Saharans. Polisario also claims that two-thirds of the 150,000 inhabitants of the Moroccan-held areas are immigrants not eligible to vote, but <LOCATION> Morocco </LOCATION> claims 90 percent of them are Western Saharans. <LOCATION> Morocco </LOCATION>'s army has kept Polisario from major gains, mainly by building a series of defensive walls in the desert. But <PERSON> King </PERSON> <PERSON> Hassan </PERSON> <PERSON> II </PERSON>'s war effort has been costing up to $ 2 million a day in recent years.
