<PERSON> Mieczyslaw </PERSON> <PERSON> Laskowski </PERSON>, interviewed by state television, noted that <PERSON> Stalowa </PERSON> <PERSON> Wola </PERSON> is a defense industry plant serving <LOCATION> Poland </LOCATION> and its socialist allies, and said no country in the world allowed strikes at such facilities. `` The situation can not tolerated ad infinitum,'' he said.
