<TEXT>
 The government said Tuesday its chief forecasting gauge of future economic activity suffered the steepest drop in eight months in July, but few analysts expect a substantial slackening in growth anytime soon. The 0.8 percent decline in the <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>'s Index of Leading Economic Indicators was the biggest since last November, when the index dropped 1.0 percent in the aftermath of the October stock market crash. However, economists noted that the index posted an exceptionally strong increase in June and cautioned against reading too much into a one-month downturn.
