<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> intends to continue emphasizing its submarine force in the future and is envisioning high-speed submarines equipped with thermal - and laser-homing torpedoes to hunt and destroy <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> subs, according to a new Russian book now being studied in the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> The Soviets are setting goals to build submarines that can travel at 50 to 60 knots underwater `` in the near term'' and ultimately up to 100 knots, while diving to depths of 6,600 feet and carrying torpedoes that can travel at 300 knots. The Soviet navy also expects to begin playing more of a role in strategic air defense by deploying futuristic weapons such as lasers and particle beam guns aboard its ships, the book says.
