<HEAD>Flight Attendants Ask DOT to Investigate Icahn's Fitness</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MARJORIE ANDERS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Carl </PERSON> <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> is using <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION> as his personal cash cow to the detriment of the airline and public safety, the flight attendants union charged Tuesday. The union asked the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Transportation </ORGANIZATION> to block <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON>'s plan to take <ORGANIZATION> Trans </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> private and to freeze <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION> assets while it investigates his fitness to continue managing the airline. <PERSON> Vicki </PERSON> <PERSON> Frankovich </PERSON>, president of the <ORGANIZATION> Independent </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Federation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Flight </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Attendants </ORGANIZATION>, charged that since <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> took control of <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION> a little more than two years ago, he has `` milked'' the airline's cash reserves and sold off assets to finance his stock market and takeover ventures rather than buy new airplanes and other safety equipment needed to assure <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION>'s future Through spokesman <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Allen </PERSON>, <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> called <ORGANIZATION> IFFA </ORGANIZATION>'s allegations `` spurious, malicious and erroneous'' and designed `` to embarrass the airline.'' `` Today <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION> has more planes, serves more airports and carries more passengers than in 1986,'' <PERSON> Allen </PERSON> said in a formal statement. Still, <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION>'s fleet remains the oldest in the industry; the average plane is 14.6 years old, the union said. A <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Boeing </ORGANIZATION> 727 that landed on its belly Saturday in <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> when its landing gear failed to descend was 24 years old, according to the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Transportation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Safety </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION>, which still is investigating the cause of that incident. The union criticized <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION>'s plans to spend just 1 percent of the gross value of its fleet on new equipment this year while other airlines are spending about 15 or 20 percent on new, fuel-efficient planes. This, the union says, contributes to high maintenance costs and the airline's accident and incident rate, which according to the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aviation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION> is the worst among the top 10 American airlines. Old airplanes also cost more to maintain than new ones and <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION> will have to spend more and more to keep its planes safe, the union says. `` This would require a healthy cash flow,'' <PERSON> Frankovich </PERSON> said. `` But according to disclosures in <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON>'s own filings before the <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION>'s cash flow is not expected to be sufficient to repay the increased debt to be incurred under his privatization plan.'' <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON>, who owns 75 percent of <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION>'s stock, will ask minority shareholders at a meeting Sept. 7 to sell their stock to him. Payments would be financed by the sale of $ 250 million in speculative, high-yield bonds. This would raise <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION>'s annual interest payments to $ 466 million, almost double the airline's 1987 operating earnings of $ 240 million, according to <ORGANIZATION> IFFA </ORGANIZATION>'s analysis. In addition, for his <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION> stock, <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> would receive $ 400 million in <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION> assets, including a big chunk of <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> stock, the union said. `` <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION> is being managed today not as an air carrier but as an unsupervised mutual fund benefiting Mr. <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON>,'' <PERSON> Frankovich </PERSON> said. `` Unless the <ORGANIZATION> DOT </ORGANIZATION> acts now to stop him, <PERSON> Carl </PERSON> <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> and his companies will take $ 650 million out of an already weakened <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION> and leave the flying public, his creditors and his long-suffering employees to reap the sad and perhaps tragic consequences,'' she added. <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON>, in his statement, said: `` I have no doubt that <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION> employees, the traveling public and the appropriate government officials will see through <ORGANIZATION> IFFA </ORGANIZATION>'s meritless charges and understand <ORGANIZATION> IFFA </ORGANIZATION>'s motivation.'' <ORGANIZATION> TWA </ORGANIZATION>'s machinists union, which also opposes the privatization and filed suit in federal court last week to stop it, is being asked to join the IFFA petition but has not yet had time to study it, <PERSON> Frankovich </PERSON> said. Unions at <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> made a similar request to the DOT last year. In its findings the <ORGANIZATION> DOT </ORGANIZATION> said acrimonious relations between labor and management could lead to operational problems and a former <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Secretary of Labor was appointed to act as a mediator.
