<HEAD>Continental Introduces Money-Back Guarantee; New Companion Fare</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>, seeking to lure business travelers wary of its reputation for poor service, on Tuesday announced a new money-back service guarantee for first-class passengers. Under the program, effective Sept. 19 through Oct. 31, first-class fliers can get a refund of as much as $ 200 if they are not satisfied with any aspect of their domestic flights, from making reservations to claiming their baggage when they arrive. <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> said the unconditional service refund is the first such guarantee offered by a <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> airline. Passengers are entitled to a refund if they are unhappy with in-flight meals, if flights are delayed or for any other reason. `` There are no questions asked; there's no fine print,'' <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> President <PERSON> Martin </PERSON> <PERSON> Shugrue </PERSON> told a news conference. `` We're willing to put our money on the line.'' Houston-based <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION>, a subsidiary of giant <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, generally is known for its aggressive fare cutting. <PERSON> Shugrue </PERSON> conceded it was no secret that <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> suffered from a reputation for inferior service. However, he said, the airline has improved its on-time performance so it now ranks third among the major carriers, according to government statistics. The airline was in last place this past winter. The airline's poor service record `` is all history,'' <PERSON> Shugrue </PERSON> said. `` We have total confidence in our service product.'' <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> also announced a new fare of $ 79 each way for companions of passengers traveling on its MaxSaver discount fares anywhere in the mainland <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. The companion fare can be used for travel between Sept. 7 and Dec. 15. A $ 79 companion fare also was announced by Miami-based <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>, the other major carrier owned by <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION>. Eastern said the new Companion MaxSaver, valid during the same period, will reduce the cost of two people traveling together by more than 30 percent. <ORGANIZATION> Northwest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>, a competitor, said it was matching the $ 79 companion fares for vacation travelers `` who are looking for a fall fling.'' <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> also introduced a 10 percent discount for passengers over age 65 for travel within the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> mainland, and two year-long tickets for senior citizens allowing unlimited travel within the mainland for $ 1,299 and worldwide for $ 2,299. In addition, <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> said it is cutting its unrestricted fares by as much as 70 percent and simplifying its price structure on nonstop flights between <LOCATION> Denver </LOCATION> and 38 cities. <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> is striving to increase its market share in <LOCATION> Denver </LOCATION>, one of its major hubs. Chicago-based <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION>'s main competitor in <LOCATION> Denver </LOCATION>, said Tuesday it planned to match fare cuts in that market. Under the money-back guarantee, passengers must submit a refund form available from ticket agents. Fliers will receive refund checks in about six to eight weeks, <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> said. The offer is limited to three refunds per passenger. <PERSON> Shugrue </PERSON> said there is a strong possibility the guarantee program could be extended beyond the Oct. 31 expiration. Passengers who paid $ 500 to $ 699 for first-class, round-trip tickets are eligible for a $ 100 refund. Fliers who paid $ 700 to $ 899 can get back $ 150, and those paying more than $ 900 are entitled to $ 200.
